In this section, we're going to examine what roles and working groups are available to you. You now have time set aside by your employer to spend on Open edX community work - how are you going to spend those hours? Where are you going to find work to do? Some options are to assist other CCs with their work, join other working groups, or look at the roadmap for potential areas of collaboration.

Consider helping out all around the community, even outside the area of your expertise - your knowledge may bring a welcome perspective to other teams.  Always feel free to attend a working group for just for a meeting or two, especially if you are currently working in an area that overlaps with that group’s domain, or you'd like to meet new community members!
